        {
          "reviewTitle": "Nice but not perfect",
          "reviewText": "I purchased the SHEGLAM Hydrating Cream Full Coverage Foundation Balm in the color Fair. The color is very forgiving and does not have a yellow or orange cast, nor does it seem to oxidize. It is definitely full coverage but can be sheared out if desired. It is lightweight and comfortable. The only con is that the formula in the packaging is dry and not quite so easy to blend but this does not take away from the beautiful coverage or almost flawless skin finish. Just makes it a little more difficult to work with. If you can get past the blending part, it is quite a beautiful foundation balm. Does not make the skin feel dry at all and is not cakey. Long lasting formula.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2024",
          "customer": "LEE C.",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHGPPPC5K77I34A73K7W6HPTV4EQ",
