        {
          "reviewTitle": "Not a good foundation for mature skin",
          "reviewText": "I wasn't expecting much when I ordered this. I'm 57 and my skin has changed, so I'm always on the lookout for a good foundation. Powder types are horrible for mature skin, I haven't found a serum type I like. Liquid foundations are hit or miss. I thought for the price if it didn't work out I could give it to my daughter, who is a makeup hoarder lol Well, she got this one as well. Looks great on her younger skin, but not on mature skin. I will say the color match was very good(fair/medium, neutral skin tone). It is buildable, but settled into all the fine lines and even with setting spray didn't last long. Again, it works great for my daughter who's in her 30's, but for it definitely wasn't for my mature skin.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2025",
